  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. The model is intended to identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Intended use is bounded to steady-state, single-phase Newtonian blood surrogate at nominal CPB flow rates (3–6 L/min) and rotational speeds (2000–3500 RPM); results support design-phase comparative ranking only and are not intended for patient-specific dosimetry.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/hemolysis-worst-case-identification",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-hemolysis-cfd-credible-mrl2",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/fda-gcbp-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-gcbp-piv-experimental-2013",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-gcbp-hemolysis-bench-2015"
  ],
